# CLAUDE.md - WikiDocs Interactive Documentation Platform

## Platform Overview

WikiDocs is a revolutionary interactive documentation and testing platform that optimizes AI-human collaboration through flow state enablement. Built on the Katalyst framework, it transforms how teams create, maintain, and interact with technical documentation by integrating real-time testing, interactive components, and AI coding acceleration within the autonogrammer ecosystem.

## Architecture & Technology Stack

### Core Technologies
- **Framework**: Katalyst-based architecture with React 19 and concurrent features
- **Runtime**: Deno 2.0+ (primary) with Node.js 18+ compatibility
- **Build System**: Vite with Turborepo for monorepo optimization
- **Package Manager**: Bun 1.0+ for fast dependency management
- **Content**: MDX 3 for interactive documentation with embedded components
- **Diagrams**: XYFlow/ReactFlow for interactive flow visualizations
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom design system
- **Testing**: Vitest with Playwright for E2E testing

### Infrastructure
```
wikidocs/
├── apps/
│   ├── docs/              # Main documentation site
│   ├── playground/        # Interactive testing playground  
│   ├── dashboard/         # Flow state and metrics dashboard
│   └── api/              # Backend API services
├── packages/
│   ├── wikidocs-core/     # Core engine and orchestration
│   ├── mdx-components/    # Interactive MDX components
│   ├── testing-framework/ # AI code testing infrastructure
│   ├── flow-state/       # Flow state optimization engine
│   ├── xyflow-components/ # Interactive flow diagrams
│   └── github-actions/    # CI/CD integration workflows
├── docs/                 # Platform documentation
└── examples/             # Interactive documentation examples
```

### Key Services & Components

#### Interactive Documentation Engine
```typescript
// Core MDX processing and component system
interface DocumentationEngine {
  mdx: MDXProcessor;
  components: InteractiveComponents;
  testing: RealTimeTestExecution;
  collaboration: LiveEditing;
}

// Interactive component registry
class ComponentRegistry {
  register(name: string, component: React.ComponentType): void;

  // Built-in interactive components
  components = {
    InteractiveTest: CodeExecutionComponent,
    CodeFlow: FlowDiagramComponent, 
    DependencyGraph: DependencyVisualization,
    AIMetrics: AIPerformanceMetrics,
    FlowState: ProductivityMonitoring
  };
}
```

#### AI Collaboration Framework
```typescript
// AI coding assistance and testing
interface AICollaborationSystem {
  testing: AICodeTestingFramework;
  metrics: AIEffectivenessTracking;
  flowState: DeveloperProductivityOptimization;
  automation: DocumentationGeneration;
}

// AI code quality assessment
class AITestingFramework {
  async validateCode(
    code: string, 
    context: CodeContext, 
    aiProvider: AIProvider
  ): Promise<ValidationResult> {
    const syntaxCheck = await this.validateSyntax(code);
    const logicCheck = await this.validateLogic(code, context);
    const performanceCheck = await this.analyzePerformance(code);

    return {
      syntaxCorrectness: syntaxCheck.score,
      logicalCorrectness: logicCheck.score,
      performanceScore: performanceCheck.score,
      suggestions: this.generateImprovements(code, context)
    };
  }
}
```

### Autonogrammer Ecosystem Integration

#### Interactive Documentation Hub Role
```yaml
Platform Role: "Interactive Documentation & AI Collaboration Platform"
Integration Points:
  - Real-time synchronization with GitBook for content publishing
  - Chatwoot integration for customer support documentation
  - GitLab CI/CD for automated documentation generation
  - Flow diagram integration with pro-platform XYFlow components
  - AI-powered content generation and testing validation
```

#### Flow State Optimization Engine
```typescript
// Developer productivity and focus optimization
interface FlowStateSystem {
  monitoring: FocusSessionTracking;
  optimization: ContextSwitchingMinimization;
  analytics: ProductivityMetrics;
  recommendations: FlowStateImprovements;
}

// Real-time flow state tracking
class FlowStateMonitor {
  async trackDeveloperSession(userId: string): Promise<FlowStateData> {
    return {
      focusTime: this.measureFocusTime(),
      contextSwitches: this.countContextSwitches(),
      aiInteractions: this.trackAIAssistance(),
      codeQuality: this.assessCodeQuality(),
      productivityScore: this.calculateProductivityScore()
    };
  }

  async optimizeWorkflow(userId: string): Promise<OptimizationSuggestions> {
    const currentState = await this.getCurrentFlowState(userId);
    const historicalData = await this.getHistoricalFlowData(userId);

    return this.generateOptimizationRecommendations(currentState, historicalData);
  }
}
```

## Core Features & Capabilities

### Interactive MDX Components
```typescript
// Comprehensive interactive component system
interface InteractiveComponents {
  codeExecution: {
    InteractiveTest: "Live code testing within documentation";
    CodePlayground: "Interactive code editing and execution";
    TestRunner: "Automated test execution and reporting";
    PerformanceBenchmark: "Code performance measurement";
